showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:0}); // Ester
“Hmm, so that's what happened.
I'll talk to Dio directly.
You just concentrate on the race.”{PAUSE}“Oh yeah, getting back to the other thing,
there are many different
types of Chocobo jockeys.
It's not only for criminals.”{PAUSE}“Some people compete for the fame,
some people compete for the money,
some only for glory…
And then there're people like you.”{PAUSE}“Oh yeah,
I'll teach you how to
ride a Chocobo.”

showWindowWithDialog({window:1, dialog:2}); // Ester
“Ummm…
First use {PURPLE}[ASSIST]{WHITE}
to choose either AUTO or MANUAL.”{PAUSE}“This lets you control the Chocobo
yourself or lets it run on its own.”{PAUSE}“But it's pretty hard to make the
Chocobo run the way you want it to.
If the Chocobo doesn't like you,
it won't listen.”{PAUSE}“Then, you're stuck…”{PAUSE}“But, most of the Chocobos
I have are mellow
and you should be able to
handle them.”{PAUSE}“When you're riding,
use {PURPLE}[SWITCH]{WHITE} to Speed Up
and {PURPLE}[CANCEL]{WHITE} to Slow Down.”{PAUSE}“But, if you go faster than
the Chocobo can handle, it will
quickly lose its stamina.”{PAUSE}“Use the Directional button to
move the Chocobo left and right,
use {PURPLE}[OK]{WHITE}
to get a boost of speed.”{PAUSE}“But this makes your stamina
run out faster.”{PAUSE}“Some Chocobos are bad-tempered
and can't pace themselves.
They'll lose their
stamina quickly.”{PAUSE}“Those Chocobos should be
set on Manual
to slow them down.”{PAUSE}“Finally, some advice
for the restless. Once
the first and second Chocobo
cross the goal line,”{PAUSE}“push {PURPLE}[START]{WHITE}
to end the race.”
